Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

While the kettle boils, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into 2cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}, pepper chunks and onion to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and the veg has softened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @jasmine rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Drain the @king prawns{150%g}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Once the chicken is golden and the veg has softened, add the garlic to the pan and fry until fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the @ketjap manis{25%g}, @gochujang paste{50%g}, @honey{15%g}, @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} and @water{50%ml}(for the sauce) into the chicken and veg.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Squeeze in some lime juice from a lime wedge. Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lime juice if needed.

Add a splash of @water{} if you feel it needs it.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over the sweet and sticky chicken and prawn stir-fry.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!